Android OpenGL ES,
http://developer.android.com/guide/topics/graphics/opengl.html
Android includes support for high performance 2D and 3D graphics with the Open Graphics Library (OpenGLÂ®), specifically, the OpenGL ES API. OpenGL is a cross-platform graphics API that specifies a standard software interface for 3D graphics processing hardware.
Android supports several versions of the OpenGL ES API:
OpenGL ES 1.0 and 1.1 - This API specification is supported by Android 1.0 and higher. 
OpenGL ES 2.0 - This API specification is supported by Android 2.2 (API level 8) and higher. 
OpenGL ES 3.0 - This API specification is supported by Android 4.3 (API level 18) and higher. 
OpenGL ES 3.1 - This API specification is supported by Android 5.0 (API level 21) and higher.

